    "body" : "<p>Something missing from gipinani's answer</p>\n\n<pre><code>@Scheduled(cron = \"0 1 1,13 * * ?\", zone = \"CST\")\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This will execute at 1.01 and 13.01. It can be used when you need to run the job without a pattern multiple times a day.</p>\n\n<p>And the zone attribute is very useful, when you do deployments in remote servers. This was introduced with spring 4.</p>\n"
