      "post_id" : 37966649,
      "comment_id" : 104230272,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "You should be careful about the timezones. If you want to set a default timezone for your whole app, I suggest you to set the timezone of the OS that your application is running on. Spring app will use the timezone of the OS. I generally use UTC on machines and apply all date-time values in UTC zone. <code>spring.jackson.time-zone=IST</code> should also work but I am not sure, please check it with a unit test."
