    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 140,
    "last_activity_date" : 1466594752,
    "creation_date" : 1466594752,
    "answer_id" : 37966649,
    "question_id" : 26147044,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>For my scheduler, I am using it to fire at 6 am every day and my cron notation is:</p>\n\n<pre><code>0 0 6 * * *\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>If you want 1:01:am then set it to</p>\n\n<pre><code>0 1 1 * * *\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Complete code for the scheduler</p>\n\n<pre><code>@Scheduled(cron=\"0 1 1 * * *\")\npublic void doScheduledWork() {\n    //complete scheduled work\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>** <strong>VERY IMPORTANT</strong></p>\n\n<p>To be sure about the firing time correctness of your scheduler, you have to set zone value like this (I am in Istanbul):</p>\n\n<pre><code>@Scheduled(cron=\"0 1 1 * * *\", zone=\"Europe/Istanbul\")\npublic void doScheduledWork() {\n    //complete scheduled work\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>You can find the complete time zone values from <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/cd/B13866_04/webconf.904/b10877/timezone.htm\" rel=\"noreferrer\">here</a>.</p>\n\n<p>Note: My Spring framework version is: 4.0.7.RELEASE</p>\n"
